        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>Rule 10.4.  Putting the question
Questions shall be distinctly put in this form: &quot;As many of you as are in favor (here the question is stated) shall vote 'Yes'; those opposed shall vote 'No.' The Clerk shall open the machine.&quot; After the roll call is recorded, the presiding officer shall then rise and state the decision of the House.
Mason's Manual:  Sec. 523
HR 3, 1973.</p>
        </content>
